name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: ipc.client.kill.max
description: Defines the maximum number of clients to disconnect in one go.

name: hadoop.caller.context.signature.max.size
description:
The caller's signature (optional) is for offline validation. If the
      signature exceeds the maximum allowed bytes in server, the caller context
      will be abandoned, in which case the caller context will not be recorded
      in audit logs.

name: dfs.namenode.fs-limits.max-xattrs-per-inode
description: Maximum number of extended attributes per inode.

name: dfs.client.read.short.circuit.replica.stale.threshold.ms
description: Threshold in milliseconds for read entries during short-circuit local reads.

name: hadoop.security.key.default.bitlength
description:
The length (bits) of keys we want the KeyProvider to produce. Key length
    defines the upper-bound on an algorithm's security, ideally, it would
    coincide with the lower-bound on an algorithm's security.

name: dfs.qjournal.select-input-streams.timeout.ms
description: Timeout in milliseconds for accepting streams from JournalManagers.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.loadedjobs.cache.size
description:
Size of the loaded job cache.  This property is ignored if
  the property mapreduce.jobhistory.loadedtasks.cache.size is set to a
  positive value.
